  "text": "where ρ(r, t) and j(r, t) are the local particle density and local current respectively. Here we consider for the space variable, the d-dimensional unit interval Ω = [0, 1] d which leads to the LDP for fluctuations of the global current as stated in Eq. [CITATION_1] . As in the main text, we consider a diffusive system in contact with two particle reservoirs with densities obeying ρ l > ρ r in the x-direction, and periodic boundary conditions in every other direction.",
